column100:
I have a degree which includes Spanish with Social Sciences and I
      lived in Mexico and studied in Mexico. I studied Spanish throughout
      school for 5 years and at university level for 4 years. I also during my
      teens, went to Spain a lot for holidays and to practice Spanish and went
      to a summer school called Don Quijote. Ps my heritage/or background is
      Caribbean British, (my parents are from multiple Caribbean Islands, but I
      was born in the UK, my father was born abroad in Jamaica and my mother
      was born in the UK.
column102: English (Jamaican Patois - which sounds like broken English)

column101:
I had a girlfriend in highschool from Spain that got me interested in
      learning Spanish, while dating it was also mandatory for me to take
      foreign language classes. I always held an interest in the language but
      at 29 I married a wonderful woman from Venazuela. I have been studying
      with a moderate intensity since then.
column102:
My English is heavy on the Southern dialect. Little colloquialisms
      that other parts of the U.S may not know.
